<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-09-10T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-09-10T22:00:00-05:00" n="947" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d947">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">890F.515/44a: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-09-10T23:00:00-04:00">September
                                    10, 1943—11 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1323. From Treasury for Gunter. Please repeat to Jidda. For your
                            information: <list>
                                <label>1.</label>
                                <item>We are trying to arrange that the United Kingdom shall pay
                                    both the minting costs and the transportation costs for the
                                    initial 8 million riyals in return for a reciprocal lend-lease
                                    credit from the United States. This Government will extend to
                                    Saudi Arabia as additional lend-lease aid by this Government the
                                    minting and transportation costs for any riyals coined
                                    here.</item>
                                <label>2.</label>
                                <item>The riyals minted in India and in London are to be delivered
                                    to Moose and presented by him to the appropriate officials of
                                    Saudi Arabia. The State Department will determine the
                                    appropriate officials to sign the receipts on behalf of Saudi
                                    Arabia upon delivery of the riyals. [Treasury.]</item>
                            </list>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>